  "label": "Lantern Berthcell",
  "description": "Lantern Berthcell forms a compact sleeping chamber recessed behind pressure-rated bulkheads within The Index Lantern’s modular shell. The walls carry fine transit-index inlay continued from the tavern vaulting, while radiant conductor-ribs frame a narrow berth and a fold-down work ledge. Acoustic baffles and gasketed seams suppress the station’s docking-gallery vibration, preserving the tavern’s engineered, unvarying gloom. A sealed wash niche and stowage recesses emphasize short-layover function within Continuum Anchorage’s causality-safe regime.",
